headline: 3 Consumer Stocks Walking a Fine Line
summary: The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. Unfortunately, the industry’s recent performance suggests demand may be fading as discretionary stocks have pulled back by 11.4% over the past six months. This performance was worse than the S&P 500’s 6.2% loss.
